Candidate Submission Guidelines
General Structure
Component Naming
Use clear and descriptive names for components, classes, and IDs.
Ensure proper folder structure for components (e.g., /components, /pages, /styles).
CSS Class Rules
Allowed Class Naming:
Vanilla CSS: All classes must start with .food- (e.g., .food-card, .food-status).
Tailwind: Custom classes must include the food- prefix (e.g., food-btn, food-item).
Test ID Convention
All test IDs must start with food-
Example: data-test-id="food-delete-btn"
Mandatory Test Coverage
Candidates must write tests for at least 3 critical scenarios, covering:
Component Rendering
Verify that the component renders correctly with expected props (e.g., displays food name, price, or rating).
User Interaction
Test one interactive element (choose either):
Button click (e.g., delete, edit, or submit actions).
Form input and submission
API Mocking
Test one API-related behavior (choose either):
Successful data fetch and display (e.g., mock GET request).
Error handling (e.g., failed API request shows error message).
.API calls must be mocked (no real network requests in tests)
